article.headline: Dayton 65, Saint Louis 64, 2OT
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Brian Roberts hit a 3-pointer and made two free throws in the final 47 seconds of double overtime to lead Dayton to a 65-64 win over Saint Louis on Saturday night. Roberts finished with 16 points to lead the Flyers (18-11, 8-8 Atlantic 10). Charles Little and Andres Sandoval each added 14. Saint Louis senior Ian Vouyoukas led all scorers with 28 points. Kevin Lisch, who missed a 3-point attempt with nine seconds left and the Billikens trailing 65-62, finished with 15 and Luke Meyer added 11. The Billikens (18-12, 8-8) shot 42 percent for the game and committed 12 turnovers. Dayton shot 37 percent and had five turnovers.
